{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":444,"text":"When I was President of the American\nPsychological Association,"},{"time":3540,"text":"they tried to media-train me."},{"time":5190,"text":"And an encounter I had with CNN summarizes"},{"time":10890,"text":"what I'm going to be talking about today,"},{"time":12902,"text":"which is the eleventh reason\nto be optimistic."},{"time":16000,"text":"The editor of Discover told us 10 of them;"},{"time":22199,"text":"I'm going to give you the eleventh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24318,"text":"So they came to me, CNN,\nand they said, \"Professor Seligman --"},{"time":29550,"text":"would you tell us about the state\nof psychology today?"},{"time":32787,"text":"We'd like to interview you about that.\""},{"time":34728,"text":"And I said, \"Great.\""},{"time":35966,"text":"And she said, \"But this is CNN,\nso you only get a sound bite.\""},{"time":41309,"text":"I said, \"Well, how many words do I get?\""},{"time":44547,"text":"And she said, \"Well, one.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":46208,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":48018,"text":"And the cameras rolled, and she said,"},{"time":50381,"text":"\"Professor Seligman,\nwhat is the state of psychology today?\""},{"time":55228,"text":"\"Good.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":56411,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":58563,"text":"\"Cut! Cut. That won't do."},{"time":62904,"text":"We'd really better give\nyou a longer sound bite.\""},{"time":65710,"text":"\"How many words do I get this time?\""},{"time":67464,"text":"\"Well, you get two.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":68904,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":70660,"text":"\"Doctor Seligman, what is the state\nof psychology today?\""},{"time":75607,"text":"\"Not good.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":76803,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":88557,"text":"\"Look, Doctor Seligman,"},{"time":89753,"text":"we can see you're really\nnot comfortable in this medium."},{"time":92771,"text":"We'd better give you a real sound bite."},{"time":95184,"text":"This time you can have three words."},{"time":98289,"text":"Professor Seligman, what is the state\nof psychology today?\""},{"time":103202,"text":"\"Not good enough.\""},{"time":106005,"text":"That's what I'm going to be talking about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108113,"text":"I want to say why psychology\nwas good, why it was not good,"},{"time":112246,"text":"and how it may become,\nin the next 10 years, good enough."},{"time":116742,"text":"And by parallel summary, I want to say\nthe same thing about technology,"},{"time":121078,"text":"about entertainment and design,"},{"time":122807,"text":"because I think the issues\nare very similar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125335,"text":"So, why was psychology good?"},{"time":128387,"text":"Well, for more than 60 years, psychology\nworked within the disease model."},{"time":133000,"text":"Ten years ago, when I was on an airplane"},{"time":135000,"text":"and I introduced myself to my seatmate,\nand told them what I did,"},{"time":139047,"text":"they'd move away from me,"},{"time":141862,"text":"because, quite rightly, they were saying"},{"time":144337,"text":"psychology is about finding\nwhat's wrong with you."},{"time":146960,"text":"Spot the loony."},{"time":148395,"text":"And now, when I tell people\nwhat I do, they move toward me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152791,"text":"What was good about psychology --"},{"time":157204,"text":"about the $30 billion\ninvestment NIMH made,"},{"time":160250,"text":"about working in the disease model,"},{"time":162000,"text":"about what you mean by psychology --"},{"time":164481,"text":"is that, 60 years ago,\nnone of the disorders were treatable;"},{"time":168895,"text":"it was entirely smoke and mirrors."},{"time":170831,"text":"And now, 14 of the disorders\nare treatable,"},{"time":173318,"text":"two of them actually curable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175731,"text":"And the other thing that happened\nis that a science developed,"},{"time":180480,"text":"a science of mental illness."},{"time":182432,"text":"We found out we could take fuzzy concepts"},{"time":187232,"text":"like depression, alcoholism,"},{"time":190236,"text":"and measure them with rigor;"},{"time":192269,"text":"that we could create a classification\nof the mental illnesses;"},{"time":196444,"text":"that we could understand\nthe causality of the mental illnesses."},{"time":201149,"text":"We could look across time\nat the same people --"},{"time":205000,"text":"people, for example, who were genetically\nvulnerable to schizophrenia --"},{"time":209001,"text":"and ask what the contribution\nof mothering, of genetics are,"},{"time":214237,"text":"and we could isolate third variables"},{"time":216625,"text":"by doing experiments\non the mental illnesses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219489,"text":"And best of all, we were able,\nin the last 50 years,"},{"time":223015,"text":"to invent drug treatments\nand psychological treatments."},{"time":227722,"text":"And then we were able\nto test them rigorously,"},{"time":231000,"text":"in random-assignment,\nplacebo-controlled designs,"},{"time":234317,"text":"throw out the things that didn't work,"},{"time":236593,"text":"keep the things that actively did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238696,"text":"The conclusion of that is,"},{"time":241883,"text":"psychology and psychiatry\nof the last 60 years"},{"time":245000,"text":"can actually claim that we can make\nmiserable people less miserable."},{"time":250658,"text":"And I think that's terrific."},{"time":252834,"text":"I'm proud of it."},{"time":257833,"text":"But what was not good,\nthe consequences of that,"},{"time":261515,"text":"were three things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262955,"text":"The first was moral;"},{"time":264757,"text":"that psychologists and psychiatrists\nbecame victimologists, pathologizers;"},{"time":269575,"text":"that our view of human nature\nwas that if you were in trouble,"},{"time":272641,"text":"bricks fell on you."},{"time":274414,"text":"And we forgot that people\nmade choices and decisions."},{"time":277179,"text":"We forgot responsibility."},{"time":279068,"text":"That was the first cost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281217,"text":"The second cost was\nthat we forgot about you people."},{"time":285521,"text":"We forgot about improving normal lives."},{"time":289100,"text":"We forgot about a mission to make\nrelatively untroubled people happier,"},{"time":295000,"text":"more fulfilled, more productive."},{"time":297804,"text":"And \"genius,\" \"high-talent,\"\nbecame a dirty word."},{"time":301527,"text":"No one works on that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303562,"text":"And the third problem\nabout the disease model is,"},{"time":307000,"text":"in our rush to do something\nabout people in trouble,"},{"time":310305,"text":"in our rush to do something\nabout repairing damage,"},{"time":315433,"text":"it never occurred to us\nto develop interventions"},{"time":318072,"text":"to make people happier --\npositive interventions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322335,"text":"So that was not good."},{"time":324200,"text":"And so that's what led people\nlike Nancy Etcoff, Dan Gilbert,"},{"time":329053,"text":"Mike Csikszentmihalyi and myself"},{"time":330986,"text":"to work in something I call,\n\"positive psychology,\""},{"time":333870,"text":"which has three aims."},{"time":335679,"text":"The first is that psychology\nshould be just as concerned"},{"time":340589,"text":"with human strength\nas it is with weakness."},{"time":344000,"text":"It should be just as concerned\nwith building strength"},{"time":348670,"text":"as with repairing damage."},{"time":350832,"text":"It should be interested\nin the best things in life."},{"time":353539,"text":"And it should be just as concerned"},{"time":355437,"text":"with making the lives\nof normal people fulfilling,"},{"time":359174,"text":"and with genius,\nwith nurturing high talent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364068,"text":"So in the last 10 years\nand the hope for the future,"},{"time":368575,"text":"we've seen the beginnings\nof a science of positive psychology,"},{"time":372000,"text":"a science of what makes life worth living."},{"time":374539,"text":"It turns out that we can measure\ndifferent forms of happiness."},{"time":379108,"text":"And any of you, for free,\ncan go to that website --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":382612,"text":"[www.authentichappiness.org]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":384027,"text":"and take the entire panoply\nof tests of happiness."},{"time":386530,"text":"You can ask, how do you stack\nup for positive emotion, for meaning,"},{"time":391000,"text":"for flow, against literally tens\nof thousands of other people?"},{"time":395718,"text":"We created the opposite of the diagnostic\nmanual of the insanities:"},{"time":401000,"text":"a classification of the strengths\nand virtues that looks at the sex ratio,"},{"time":406245,"text":"how they're defined, how to diagnose them,"},{"time":408475,"text":"what builds them\nand what gets in their way."},{"time":413000,"text":"We found that we could discover\nthe causation of the positive states,"},{"time":417463,"text":"the relationship between left\nhemispheric activity"},{"time":421000,"text":"and right hemispheric activity,\nas a cause of happiness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428500,"text":"I've spent my life working\non extremely miserable people,"},{"time":431501,"text":"and I've asked the question:"},{"time":432912,"text":"How do extremely miserable people\ndiffer from the rest of you?"},{"time":436589,"text":"And starting about six years ago,\nwe asked about extremely happy people."},{"time":441000,"text":"How do they differ from the rest of us?"},{"time":443564,"text":"It turns out there's one way,\nvery surprising --"},{"time":447071,"text":"they're not more religious,\nthey're not in better shape,"},{"time":449763,"text":"they don't have more money,\nthey're not better looking,"},{"time":452875,"text":"they don't have more good events\nand fewer bad events."},{"time":455654,"text":"The one way in which they differ:\nthey're extremely social."},{"time":460804,"text":"They don't sit in seminars\non Saturday morning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":463529,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":467977,"text":"They don't spend time alone."},{"time":469501,"text":"Each of them is in a romantic relationship"},{"time":471723,"text":"and each has a rich repertoire of friends."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474895,"text":"But watch out here -- this is merely\ncorrelational data, not causal,"},{"time":479296,"text":"and it's about happiness\nin the first, \"Hollywood\" sense,"},{"time":482918,"text":"I'm going to talk about,"},{"time":484154,"text":"happiness of ebullience\nand giggling and good cheer."},{"time":488344,"text":"And I'm going to suggest to you\nthat's not nearly enough,"},{"time":491203,"text":"in just a moment."},{"time":493424,"text":"We found we could begin to look\nat interventions over the centuries,"},{"time":497829,"text":"from the Buddha to Tony Robbins."},{"time":499646,"text":"About 120 interventions have been proposed\nthat allegedly make people happy."},{"time":504856,"text":"And we find that we've been able\nto manualize many of them,"},{"time":509502,"text":"and we actually carry out"},{"time":511445,"text":"random-assignment efficacy\nand effectiveness studies."},{"time":515111,"text":"That is, which ones actually\nmake people lastingly happier?"},{"time":519291,"text":"In a couple of minutes, I'll tell you\nabout some of those results."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522542,"text":"But the upshot of this is that the mission\nI want psychology to have,"},{"time":529000,"text":"in addition to its mission\nof curing the mentally ill,"},{"time":532511,"text":"and in addition to its mission of making\nmiserable people less miserable,"},{"time":536809,"text":"is, can psychology actually\nmake people happier?"},{"time":540762,"text":"And to ask that question -- \"happy\"\nis not a word I use very much --"},{"time":545435,"text":"we've had to break it down"},{"time":546872,"text":"into what I think\nis askable about \"happy.\""},{"time":549428,"text":"And I believe there are three different --"},{"time":553179,"text":"I call them \"different\" because different\ninterventions build them,"},{"time":556486,"text":"it's possible to have one\nrather than the other --"},{"time":558911,"text":"three different happy lives."},{"time":560912,"text":"The first happy life is the pleasant life."},{"time":564053,"text":"This is a life in which you have\nas much positive emotion"},{"time":567462,"text":"as you possibly can,"},{"time":569000,"text":"and the skills to amplify it."},{"time":571125,"text":"The second is a life of engagement:"},{"time":573329,"text":"a life in your work, your parenting,\nyour love, your leisure;"},{"time":578718,"text":"time stops for you."},{"time":581142,"text":"That's what Aristotle was talking about."},{"time":583214,"text":"And third, the meaningful life."},{"time":585305,"text":"I want to say a little bit\nabout each of those lives"},{"time":588000,"text":"and what we know about them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":589841,"text":"The first life is the pleasant life,\nand it's simply, as best we can find it,"},{"time":594843,"text":"it's having as many\nof the pleasures as you can,"},{"time":597154,"text":"as much positive emotion as you can,"},{"time":599553,"text":"and learning the skills -- savoring,\nmindfulness -- that amplify them,"},{"time":606114,"text":"that stretch them over time and space."},{"time":609000,"text":"But the pleasant life has three drawbacks,"},{"time":613000,"text":"and it's why positive psychology\nis not happy-ology,"},{"time":616532,"text":"and why it doesn't end here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":618881,"text":"The first drawback is,\nit turns out the pleasant life,"},{"time":622000,"text":"your experience of positive emotion,"},{"time":624659,"text":"is about 50 percent heritable,"},{"time":629406,"text":"and, in fact, not very modifiable."},{"time":633000,"text":"So the different tricks\nthat Matthieu and I and others know"},{"time":637563,"text":"about increasing the amount\nof positive emotion in your life"},{"time":641198,"text":"are 15 to 20 percent tricks,\ngetting more of it."},{"time":645496,"text":"Second is that positive\nemotion habituates."},{"time":649762,"text":"It habituates rapidly, indeed."},{"time":653586,"text":"It's all like French vanilla ice cream:"},{"time":655980,"text":"the first taste is 100 percent;"},{"time":658619,"text":"by the time you're down\nto the sixth taste,"},{"time":660812,"text":"it's gone."},{"time":663657,"text":"And, as I said,\nit's not particularly malleable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":668440,"text":"And this leads to the second life."},{"time":670331,"text":"I have to tell you about my friend Len,"},{"time":672293,"text":"to talk about why positive psychology\nis more than positive emotion,"},{"time":678228,"text":"more than building pleasure."},{"time":680000,"text":"In two of the three great arenas\nof life, by the time Len was 30,"},{"time":684000,"text":"Len was enormously successful."},{"time":686448,"text":"The first arena was work."},{"time":690000,"text":"By the time he was 20,\nhe was an options trader."},{"time":692660,"text":"By the time he was 25,\nhe was a multimillionaire"},{"time":695111,"text":"and the head of an options\ntrading company."},{"time":698000,"text":"Second, in play, he's a national\nchampion bridge player."},{"time":705206,"text":"But in the third great arena of life,\nlove, Len is an abysmal failure."},{"time":710000,"text":"And the reason he was,\nwas that Len is a cold fish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":716000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":718094,"text":"Len is an introvert."},{"time":722532,"text":"American women said to Len,\nwhen he dated them,"},{"time":726000,"text":"\"You're no fun. You don't have\npositive emotion. Get lost.\""},{"time":730787,"text":"And Len was wealthy enough to be able\nto afford a Park Avenue psychoanalyst,"},{"time":736000,"text":"who for five years tried\nto find the sexual trauma"},{"time":739768,"text":"that had somehow locked\npositive emotion inside of him."},{"time":743737,"text":"But it turned out there wasn't\nany sexual trauma."},{"time":746915,"text":"It turned out that --"},{"time":749130,"text":"Len grew up in Long Island"},{"time":751533,"text":"and he played football\nand watched football, and played bridge."},{"time":758376,"text":"Len is in the bottom five percent\nof what we call positive affectivities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":762610,"text":"The question is: Is Len unhappy?"},{"time":764658,"text":"And I want to say, not."},{"time":766427,"text":"Contrary to what psychology told us"},{"time":769410,"text":"about the bottom 50 percent\nof the human race in positive affectivity,"},{"time":773586,"text":"I think Len is one\nof the happiest people I know."},{"time":776202,"text":"He's not consigned\nto the hell of unhappiness,"},{"time":778872,"text":"and that's because Len, like most of you,"},{"time":782811,"text":"is enormously capable of flow."},{"time":784897,"text":"When he walks onto the floor\nof the American Exchange"},{"time":787895,"text":"at 9:30 in the morning,"},{"time":790158,"text":"time stops for him."},{"time":791473,"text":"And it stops till the closing bell."},{"time":793259,"text":"When the first card is played\ntill 10 days later,"},{"time":796183,"text":"when the tournament is over,"},{"time":797565,"text":"time stops for Len."}]},{"cues":[{"time":799676,"text":"And this is indeed\nwhat Mike Csikszentmihalyi"},{"time":802912,"text":"has been talking about, about flow."},{"time":804838,"text":"And it's distinct from pleasure\nin a very important way:"},{"time":808239,"text":"pleasure has raw feel -- you know\nit's happening; it's thought and feeling."},{"time":813667,"text":"But what Mike told you\nyesterday -- during flow ..."},{"time":818919,"text":"you can't feel anything."},{"time":822572,"text":"You're one with the music."},{"time":824664,"text":"Time stops."},{"time":825941,"text":"You have intense concentration."},{"time":827859,"text":"And this is indeed the characteristic\nof what we think of as the good life."},{"time":833102,"text":"And we think there's a recipe for it,"},{"time":835911,"text":"and it's knowing what\nyour highest strengths are --"},{"time":838529,"text":"again, there's a valid test"},{"time":840847,"text":"of what your five highest strengths are --"},{"time":843254,"text":"and then re-crafting your life"},{"time":846007,"text":"to use them as much as you possibly can."},{"time":849291,"text":"Re-crafting your work, your love,"},{"time":852000,"text":"your play, your friendship,\nyour parenting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":854781,"text":"Just one example."},{"time":857088,"text":"One person I worked with\nwas a bagger at Genuardi's."},{"time":861156,"text":"Hated the job."},{"time":862345,"text":"She's working her way through college."},{"time":864769,"text":"Her highest strength\nwas social intelligence."},{"time":867928,"text":"So she re-crafted bagging\nto make the encounter with her"},{"time":872667,"text":"the social highlight\nof every customer's day."},{"time":875922,"text":"Now, obviously she failed."},{"time":877662,"text":"But what she did was to take\nher highest strengths,"},{"time":881000,"text":"and re-craft work to use them\nas much as possible."},{"time":885000,"text":"What you get out of that\nis not smiley-ness."},{"time":887372,"text":"You don't look like Debbie Reynolds."},{"time":889299,"text":"You don't giggle a lot."},{"time":890727,"text":"What you get is more absorption."}]},{"cues":[{"time":894000,"text":"So, that's the second path."},{"time":896098,"text":"The first path, positive emotion;"},{"time":898474,"text":"the second path is eudaemonian flow;"},{"time":901594,"text":"and the third path is meaning."},{"time":904000,"text":"This is the most venerable\nof the happinesses, traditionally."},{"time":908000,"text":"And meaning, in this view, consists of --"},{"time":911523,"text":"very parallel to eudaemonia --"},{"time":914467,"text":"it consists of knowing\nwhat your highest strengths are,"},{"time":918054,"text":"and using them to belong to\nand in the service of"},{"time":922721,"text":"something larger than you are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":926922,"text":"I mentioned that for all three\nkinds of lives --"},{"time":931247,"text":"the pleasant life, the good life,\nthe meaningful life --"},{"time":934614,"text":"people are now\nhard at work on the question:"},{"time":936802,"text":"Are there things that lastingly\nchange those lives?"},{"time":941768,"text":"And the answer seems to be yes."},{"time":944791,"text":"And I'll just give you some samples of it."},{"time":947370,"text":"It's being done in a rigorous manner."},{"time":949558,"text":"It's being done in the same way\nthat we test drugs"},{"time":952419,"text":"to see what really works."},{"time":954513,"text":"So we do random-assignment,\nplacebo-controlled,"},{"time":959350,"text":"long-term studies\nof different interventions."},{"time":962221,"text":"Just to sample the kind of interventions\nthat we find have an effect:"},{"time":966750,"text":"when we teach people\nabout the pleasant life,"},{"time":970000,"text":"how to have more pleasure in your life,"},{"time":972000,"text":"one of your assignments\nis to take the mindfulness skills,"},{"time":976043,"text":"the savoring skills,"},{"time":978482,"text":"and you're assigned\nto design a beautiful day."},{"time":982173,"text":"Next Saturday, set a day aside,\ndesign yourself a beautiful day,"},{"time":987211,"text":"and use savoring and mindfulness\nto enhance those pleasures."},{"time":991429,"text":"And we can show in that way\nthat the pleasant life is enhanced."}]},{"cues":[{"time":997738,"text":"Gratitude visit."},{"time":1001083,"text":"I want you all to do this\nwith me now, if you would."},{"time":1003763,"text":"Close your eyes."},{"time":1006812,"text":"I'd like you to remember someone"},{"time":1011180,"text":"who did something enormously important"},{"time":1014252,"text":"that changed your life\nin a good direction,"},{"time":1018000,"text":"and who you never properly thanked."},{"time":1021147,"text":"The person has to be alive."},{"time":1024000,"text":"Now, OK, you can open your eyes."},{"time":1026187,"text":"I hope all of you have such a person."},{"time":1028545,"text":"Your assignment, when you're learning\nthe gratitude visit,"},{"time":1032167,"text":"is to write a 300-word\ntestimonial to that person,"},{"time":1036534,"text":"call them on the phone in Phoenix,"},{"time":1039161,"text":"ask if you can visit, don't tell them why."},{"time":1041832,"text":"Show up at their door,"},{"time":1044299,"text":"you read the testimonial --\neveryone weeps when this happens."},{"time":1049579,"text":"And what happens is, when we test people"},{"time":1052505,"text":"one week later, a month later,\nthree months later,"},{"time":1055648,"text":"they're both happier and less depressed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1059722,"text":"Another example is a strengths date,"},{"time":1062081,"text":"in which we get couples to identify\ntheir highest strengths"},{"time":1066287,"text":"on the strengths test,"},{"time":1067686,"text":"and then to design an evening\nin which they both use their strengths."},{"time":1072791,"text":"We find this is a strengthener\nof relationships."},{"time":1076788,"text":"And fun versus philanthropy."},{"time":1078786,"text":"It's so heartening\nto be in a group like this,"},{"time":1081530,"text":"in which so many of you have turned\nyour lives to philanthropy."},{"time":1085154,"text":"Well, my undergraduates and the people\nI work with haven't discovered this,"},{"time":1088836,"text":"so we actually have people\ndo something altruistic"},{"time":1092422,"text":"and do something fun,"},{"time":1094197,"text":"and contrast it."},{"time":1095375,"text":"And what you find\nis when you do something fun,"},{"time":1098000,"text":"it has a square wave walk set."},{"time":1099913,"text":"When you do something philanthropic\nto help another person,"},{"time":1103573,"text":"it lasts and it lasts."},{"time":1106526,"text":"So those are examples\nof positive interventions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1110680,"text":"So the next to last thing\nI want to say is:"},{"time":1115000,"text":"we're interested in how much\nlife satisfaction people have."},{"time":1118143,"text":"This is really what you're about."},{"time":1120107,"text":"And that's our target variable."},{"time":1122000,"text":"And we ask the question as a function\nof the three different lives,"},{"time":1126000,"text":"how much life satisfaction do you get?"},{"time":1128747,"text":"So we ask -- and we've done this\nin 15 replications,"},{"time":1131876,"text":"involving thousands of people:"},{"time":1134278,"text":"To what extent does\nthe pursuit of pleasure,"},{"time":1136797,"text":"the pursuit of positive emotion,"},{"time":1139143,"text":"the pleasant life,"},{"time":1140341,"text":"the pursuit of engagement,\ntime stopping for you,"},{"time":1143773,"text":"and the pursuit of meaning\ncontribute to life satisfaction?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1147171,"text":"And our results surprised us;\nthey were backward of what we thought."},{"time":1150789,"text":"It turns out the pursuit of pleasure\nhas almost no contribution"},{"time":1154317,"text":"to life satisfaction."},{"time":1156000,"text":"The pursuit of meaning is the strongest."},{"time":1158553,"text":"The pursuit of engagement\nis also very strong."},{"time":1163000,"text":"Where pleasure matters\nis if you have both engagement"},{"time":1167658,"text":"and you have meaning,"},{"time":1169291,"text":"then pleasure's the whipped\ncream and the cherry."},{"time":1171604,"text":"Which is to say, the full life --\nthe sum is greater than the parts,"},{"time":1178146,"text":"if you've got all three."},{"time":1179576,"text":"Conversely, if you have none\nof the three, the empty life,"},{"time":1182842,"text":"the sum is less than the parts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1184523,"text":"And what we're asking now is:\nDoes the very same relationship --"},{"time":1188798,"text":"physical health, morbidity,\nhow long you live and productivity --"},{"time":1193765,"text":"follow the same relationship?"},{"time":1195198,"text":"That is, in a corporation,"},{"time":1197700,"text":"is productivity a function of positive\nemotion, engagement and meaning?"},{"time":1203563,"text":"Is health a function\nof positive engagement,"},{"time":1206754,"text":"of pleasure, and of meaning in life?"},{"time":1209515,"text":"And there is reason to think the answer\nto both of those may well be yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1216204,"text":"So, Chris said that the last\nspeaker had a chance"},{"time":1220657,"text":"to try to integrate what he heard,"},{"time":1223102,"text":"and so this was amazing for me."},{"time":1224832,"text":"I've never been in a gathering like this."},{"time":1228801,"text":"I've never seen speakers stretch\nbeyond themselves so much,"},{"time":1232549,"text":"which was one of the remarkable things."},{"time":1235000,"text":"But I found that the problems\nof psychology seemed to be parallel"},{"time":1239000,"text":"to the problems of technology,\nentertainment and design"},{"time":1243239,"text":"in the following way:"},{"time":1244738,"text":"we all know that technology,\nentertainment and design"},{"time":1248244,"text":"have been and can be used\nfor destructive purposes."},{"time":1254371,"text":"We also know that technology,\nentertainment and design"},{"time":1258550,"text":"can be used to relieve misery."},{"time":1261551,"text":"And by the way, the distinction\nbetween relieving misery"},{"time":1265000,"text":"and building happiness\nis extremely important."},{"time":1268000,"text":"I thought, when I first became\na therapist 30 years ago,"},{"time":1271635,"text":"that if I was good enough\nto make someone not depressed,"},{"time":1277000,"text":"not anxious, not angry,"},{"time":1280867,"text":"that I'd make them happy."},{"time":1282902,"text":"And I never found that;"},{"time":1284301,"text":"I found the best you could ever do"},{"time":1286347,"text":"was to get to zero;"},{"time":1288350,"text":"that they were empty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1289588,"text":"And it turns out the skills of happiness,\nthe skills of the pleasant life,"},{"time":1295218,"text":"the skills of engagement,\nthe skills of meaning,"},{"time":1297613,"text":"are different from the skills\nof relieving misery."},{"time":1302335,"text":"And so, the parallel thing holds\nwith technology, entertainment"},{"time":1307730,"text":"and design, I believe."},{"time":1309327,"text":"That is, it is possible\nfor these three drivers of our world"},{"time":1316230,"text":"to increase happiness,"},{"time":1318758,"text":"to increase positive emotion."},{"time":1321670,"text":"And that's typically\nhow they've been used."},{"time":1323881,"text":"But once you fractionate\nhappiness the way I do --"},{"time":1326903,"text":"not just positive emotion,\nthat's not nearly enough --"},{"time":1330000,"text":"there's flow in life,\nand there's meaning in life."},{"time":1333506,"text":"As Laura Lee told us,"},{"time":1335000,"text":"design and, I believe,\nentertainment and technology,"},{"time":1338692,"text":"can be used to increase meaning\nengagement in life as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1343447,"text":"So in conclusion,"},{"time":1345091,"text":"the eleventh reason for optimism,"},{"time":1347542,"text":"in addition to the space elevator,"},{"time":1350741,"text":"is that I think with technology,\nentertainment and design,"},{"time":1355896,"text":"we can actually increase\nthe amount of tonnage"},{"time":1359668,"text":"of human happiness on the planet."},{"time":1362521,"text":"And if technology can,\nin the next decade or two,"},{"time":1366808,"text":"increase the pleasant life,\nthe good life and the meaningful life,"},{"time":1370696,"text":"it will be good enough."},{"time":1372210,"text":"If entertainment can be diverted\nto also increase positive emotion,"},{"time":1377967,"text":"meaning eudaemonia,"},{"time":1381085,"text":"it will be good enough."},{"time":1382548,"text":"And if design can increase\npositive emotion,"},{"time":1388582,"text":"eudaemonia, and flow and meaning,"},{"time":1391601,"text":"what we're all doing together\nwill become good enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1395164,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1396367,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}